================================================================================
DERIVED WORKS — Attribution required
================================================================================

The `SKILL.md` files bundled under
`distillation_v2/results/stable/<skill>/SKILL_round_*.md`
are *derived works* of the original Anthropic open-source skill files at
https://github.com/anthropics/skills (MIT License). Anthropic's copyright
notice and license terms apply to those derivations alongside this project's
MIT grant — see the upstream `LICENSE` file at the URL above for the
canonical text.

The original `SKILL_round_0.md` of each skill is the verbatim Anthropic
SKILL.md content. `SKILL_round_1.md` … `SKILL_round_N.md` are progressive
rewrites produced by the Skill Distillation pipeline in this repository
(Teacher = Claude Haiku 4.5, Student = Gemma 4-26B); they are co-derived from
the upstream content and from Anthropic Claude Haiku 4.5 model outputs.

================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY RUNTIME DEPENDENCIES
================================================================================

The repository runs against the following third-party packages. Each retains
its own license; copies are typically installed alongside the package in
`site-packages` (Python) or `node_modules` (Node). Most are permissive
(MIT / BSD / Apache 2.0):

Pipeline (Python, conda env `skills`):
  - anthropic           MIT          Anthropic Python SDK (Teacher + Judge calls)
  - openai              Apache 2.0   OpenAI Python SDK (Student via OpenRouter)
  - python-dotenv       BSD-3-Clause
  - click               BSD-3-Clause CLI framework
  - rich                MIT          Terminal output formatting
  - pyyaml              MIT          YAML config parsing
  - python-docx         MIT          .docx read/write for evaluator
  - pdf2image           MIT          PDF → PNG for visual judging
  - pillow              MIT-CMU/HPND Image processing

Demo backend (FastAPI service):
  - fastapi             MIT
  - uvicorn             BSD-3-Clause
  - pydantic            MIT
  - httpx               BSD-3-Clause

Demo frontend (Next.js app, pnpm):
  - next                MIT          Next.js framework
  - react / react-dom   MIT
  - tailwindcss         MIT
  - lucide-react        ISC          Icon set

Development:
  - pytest              MIT
  - pre-commit          MIT
  - ruff                MIT
  - markdownlint-cli    MIT

